President Biden has declared a major disaster in Kentucky due to severe storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from July 26, 2022, onwards. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Breathitt, Clay, Floyd, Johnson, Knott, Leslie, Letcher, Magoffin, Martin, Owsley, Perry, Pike, and Wolfe are eligible for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis for emergency protective measures. Hazard mitigation measures for the entire commonwealth are also eligible for federal funding. Brett H. Howard has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and additional counties and forms of assistance may be designated once assessments are completed. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.